# Quiz2Biz project rule

Use these guardrails for all edits in this repository.

## Core workflow

- Read and follow:
  - `CLAUDE.md`
  - `.avi-os-SKILL.md`
  - `.avi-os-coding-quality-SKILL.md`
- Prefer complete dependency and failure-point review before making changes.
- Implement and validate in one coherent pass (not trial-and-error patching).

## Architecture and contracts

- API routes must stay under `/api/v1/...`.
- Keep frontend/backend request and response contracts in parity.
- Apply project-type-aware data behavior where required by specs.
- Keep deferred legacy modules hidden from default V1 flow:
  - Evidence Registry
  - Decision Log
  - Policy Pack
  - QPG prompt generation
  - 95 percent readiness gate

## Quality and security

- TypeScript strict mode; avoid `any`.
- No hardcoded secrets, keys, passwords, or tokens.
- Validate and sanitize all external input.
- Use parameterized database access only.
- Include structured error handling and avoid leaking internals.

## Delivery expectations

- Update code, tests, and docs together when scope requires it.
- Prefer small, focused changes with clear validation evidence.
- Keep shell scripts LF-only line endings.
